text: Jean Joseph Schlegel was a long-distance runner from France. Schlegel competed at the 1952 Summer Olympics. He was born on 24 October 1925 and died on 18 February 2020.Jean Schlegel == References == Category:1925 births Category:2020 deaths Category:French athletes Category:Long-distance runners Category:Olympians for France Category:People from Rennes Category:Sportspeople from Brittany
